Is there any option available in Roslyn where the analyzer can traverse the syntax tree of the source code in an interprocedural manner?. 
For instance, consider the below program:
```
static void main()
{
     int a = 10;
     int b = 20;
     int result = add(a, b);
     int addResult = result;
     Console.Writeline(addResult);

}
private int add(int x, int y)
{
    return x + y;
}
```

Right now the Roslyn is performing a block code analysis I guess. Is there an option where the Roslyn Diagnostics can traverse the add method first like an interprocedural analysis and then traverse the last two statements of the main method?.

